
= SDL_QuitEvent =
A structure that contains the "quit requested" event.


== Data Fields ==
{|
|Uint32
|'''type'''
|SDL_QUIT
|-
|Uint32
|'''timestamp'''
|timestamp of the event
|}

== Code Examples ==
```c++
SDL_Event e;
for (;;) {
    SDL_PollEvent(&e);
    if (e.type == SDL_QUIT) {
        SDL_Log("Program quit after %i ticks", e.quit.timestamp);
        break;
    }
}
```

== Remarks ==
[[SDL_QuitEvent]] is a member of the [[SDL_Event]] union and is used when an event of type SDL_QUIT is reported.  You would access it through the event's <code>quit</code> field.

Please refer to [[SDL_EventType#SDL_QUIT|the discussion of SDL_QUIT]] for more details.

